net.akami.mask.tree

Class Branch<T extends Branch>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.akami.mask.tree.Branch<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - must be the kind of branch itself, except if the children are different kind of branches
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DerivativeBranch, FormatterBranch

    public class Branch<T extends Branch>
extends java.lang.Object
    The Branch class is a data class that handles a left part and a right part, as well as an expression and a reduced value. Extra data might be added by creating another branch class inheriting from this one.
    A couple of methods belonging to the class might be useful to redefine in children's classes, such as :
    - branchFormat(String), which defines how an input String must be formatted before being stored
    - canBeEvaluated(), which defines whether a part of the branch can be calculated or not. By default a branch can be evaluated as long as it has children (a left and a right part). Some branches such as the DerivativeBranch one have different behaviors.

      • branchFormat

        protected java.lang.String branchFormat(java.lang.String initial)
        Defines how a given expression must be formatted, before being stored as the expression field.
        The default behavior is to remove the edges brackets, except if the expression is trigonometric. See ExpressionUtils.removeEdgeBrackets(String, boolean) for further information.
        Parameters:
        initial - the initial string to format
        Returns:
        a formatted version of the initial string given
